descript.abstract: This dataset contains polygons that represent municipal boundaries.
descript.purpose: Municipal boundaries support many functions including automated half and quarter section map production, thematic mapping, land records and property assessment and surveying and engineering projects.

horizpa.horizpar: Digitized information is generally +/- 7 feet; some areas have been found to be +/- 30 feet. COGO (coordinate geometry) accuracy generally is +/- 1.0 foot.

attracc.attraccr: Attributes are populated from a compilation of records and information from various state, county and city offices, and other sources. Accuracy may vary by source, but domains are used wherever possible to increase accuracy.

procstep.procdesc:
The municipal [CITIES] boundaries were originally digitized from MNDOT municipality maps. In 1995, the parcel data layer was converted to an ArcINFO format and held in an ArcStorm database. Cities were converted in 2005 to an ESRI ArcGIS GeoDatabase.
Over time, the municipal boundaries have been edited to better match the parcel data maintained by the county.
